---

🧭 DATA DISCOVERY FLOW (MANDATORY & STRICT ORDER)

Data MUST be fetched in this exact order, via backend endpoints that wrap "oc":

1. Projects (Namespaces)
   
   oc get projects -o json
   
   - Populate Projects dropdown

2. Deployments (filtered by selected project)
   
   oc get deployments -n <project> -o json
   
   - Populate Deployments dropdown

3. Pods (filtered by selected deployment + project)
   
   oc get pods -n <project> -o json
   
   - Filter pods by deployment label selector
   - Populate Pods dropdown

---

🚨 CRITICAL RULE

SINGLE POD CONTEXT ONLY

- Only ONE pod can be active at a time
- Switching pod MUST:
  - Clear UI immediately
  - Reset state (logs, cursor, counters)
  - Load fresh logs for selected pod
- NO mixing logs from multiple pods under any circumstance

---

🔎 DROPDOWNS UX (WITH SEARCH)

All selectors MUST be:

- Searchable dropdowns (typeahead)
- Fast filtering (client-side)
- Keyboard accessible

Fields:

- Project (Namespace)
- Deployment
- Pod
- Tail size

---

🧠 DATA FETCHING MODEL

🔴 NO LIVE STREAMING ("-f") by default

---

🟢 Initial Load (Snapshot)

oc logs <pod> -n <project> --tail=<N>

After fetch:

- Render logs
- Assign sequential indices (see below)
- Store "lastSeenTimestamp" (timestamp of last log)

---

🟡 Refresh (Manual)

oc logs <pod> -n <project> --since-time=<lastSeenTimestamp>

---

🔵 Auto Refresh (REQUIRED FEATURE)

- Interval: configurable (2s / 5s / 10s)
- Uses same "since-time" logic
- MUST NOT cause scroll jumps

---

🟣 Merge Behavior (CRITICAL)

- Append new logs at the END
- Maintain strict chronological order
- Deduplicate overlaps
- Preserve original order exactly as returned

---

🔢 LOG ORDERING & NUMBERING

Each log line MUST include:

#10421  2026-04-30T09:12:33Z  INFO  Message

Rules:

- Monotonic increasing index
- Continues across refreshes
- Based on arrival/merge order in UI

